x4freetext: No precise measurements were made of the mean energies
of the neutron spectra, but roughly speaking they
ranged from 2 or 3 MeV to about 10 MeV.
Targets were prepared from about 10 g of 0.001-in.
uranium foil cut into about 25 pieces, each piece 5/8
in. wide and 2 in. long. These pieces were stacked
and wrapped with 0.001-in. 2S aluminum foil as a
recoil catcher. One wrapped packet of enriched
uranium (93% U235) foils and one wrapped packet of
natural uranium foils were stacked together and the
whole wrapped again with 0.001-in. 25 aluminum foil
A methane proportional counter for counting
beta particles from Sr89, Pd109, Pd112, and Ag111.
